    Adroit    :3 adj ¦3 having or showing cleverness or resourcefulness. ^w^ Clever, resourceful.  ⌄m⌄ Blunt, unresourceful.      >w< Þe adroit kitten knocked þe pot down to safely reach þe ground. ,w,
    Arcane    :3 adj ¦3 mysterious&w&semi known only by a few.           ^w^ Mysterious, esoteric. ⌄m⌄ Superficial, commonplace.  >w< You can accquire anyþing from þe black market, given you know þe right arcane knowledge. ,w,
    Avarice   :3 n   ¦3 insatiable desire for wealth&w&semi greediness.  ^w^ Greediness, hunger.   ⌄m⌄ Satiation, gratificiation. >w< Golden Cheese Cookie's avarice and her radiance is unmatched. ,w,
    Churlish  :3 adj ¦3 vulgar&w&semi boorish.                           ^w^ Vulgar, boorish.      ⌄m⌄ Meet, civil.               >w< Bondage in public is quite a churlish display. ,w,
    Convivial :3 adj ¦3 sociable&w&semi lively.                          ^w^ Sociable, spirited.   ⌄m⌄ Antisociable, reclusive.   >w< Þe convivial banter revived þe moribund street of Drury Lane. ,w,
